# Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your actual values.

```
# Authentication
TEST_PASSWORD=sanctuary_mode_v1
WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret_here

# Slack Integration
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-your-slack-workspace-token
SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET=your-slack-signing-secret
SLACK_CHANNEL_ID=your-channel-id

# GitHub Integration
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_github_personal_access_token
GITHUB_OWNER=your-github-username
GITHUB_REPO=slack-for-school

# LMS Integration (Canvas, Blackboard, etc.)
LMS_API_KEY=your_lms_api_key
LMS_BASE_URL=https://your-lms-instance.instructure.com
LMS_COURSE_ID=12345

# AI/ML (Optional for production)
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-key

# Observability
SENTRY_DSN=https://your-sentry-dsn
DATADOG_API_KEY=your-datadog-key

# Deployment
VERCEL_ENV=development
```

## Notes

- **TEST_PASSWORD**: Used for the MVP auth endpoint. Change this before production.
- **SLACK_BOT_TOKEN**: Get this from your Slack App config. Requires `chat:write`, `channels:read`, `users:read` scopes.
- **GITHUB_TOKEN**: Generate a personal access token with `repo` scope.
- **LMS_API_KEY**: Provided by your LMS admin.
